# cPanel: Advanced Functions

## Setup Cron Jobs

- Log on to your cPanel Interface.
- Go to ''Advanced' section.
- Click on "Cron Jobs".

```diagram

```

- Enter the email address where you want to receive cron output
- Enter the command you want the cron job to run in the blank field next to the Command 
- Select how often you want the command to be run by  selecting a predefined period from the Common Settings drop-down menu.
- Now click on Add New Cron Job

```diagram

```


## Apache Handlers

Apache handlers control how the Apache web server software manages certain file types and extensions for your site. Apache comes configured to handle CGI scripts and server-parsed files. You can configure Apache to handle a new file type with an existing handler by manually adding the handler and extension below.

- Login to cPanel of your account
- Click on Apache Handler under Advanced section

```diagram

```

- Put the  handlers and its extensions you want to add and then click on Add

```diagram

```

## Image Tool

- Log on to cPanel of your account
- Click on Image Manager under Advanced section

```diagram

```

- The Image Manager allows you to view and modify images in your account. You can change the size of your images, convert their file types, or just view them.

```diagram

```

## Index Manager

The Index Manager allows you to customize the way a directory will be viewed on the web. You can select between a default style, no indexes, or two types of indexing. If you do not wish for people to be able to see the files in your directory, choose "No Indexing".

- Log on to cPanel of your acccount.
- Click on Index manager under Advanced section

```diagram

```

- Click on the Directory name you want to customize directory index.

```diagram

```

- Select the directory listing type for that folder and then click  Save

```diagram

```
